dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi run out (Taylor) 61 (51b 7x4 1x6 81m) SR: 119.6

dismissalComment.html: direct hit and this could be tight! Afridi hits it straight to Taylor at cover and takes off immediately. There was no single in there. Once Taylor hit, it was over for him. He gets a standing ovation for a superb 61

Vettori has struck, Shehzad is gone! That was the arm ball sliding in towards the stumps from outside off, Shehzad went way back in the crease and covered his stumps, the ball came in struck him right in front of the stumps past the bat, finger went up immediately. Pakistan decide not to review it

oh another one! Younis has swept this straight to deep backward square leg. It was a late decision on Younis' part. He was upright and went down very quickly, possibly that was the reason he didn't get the control on it. Hits it hard, hits it flat .. straight to the fielder

oh my Vettori! What a stunner that is! And we thought he had fitness issues! Misbah wanted to go over the infield but gets a toe-end to his attempted loft.. dismissalComment.html: superb delivery to get rid of Hafeez, who was not looking good today! It had the scrambled seam on length outside off, Hafeez moved towards the ball and left a gap between bat and ball which the ball sneaked through, deflected off the pad and hit the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi run out (Taylor) 61 (51b 7x4 1x6 81m) SR: 119.6

dismissalComment.html: direct hit and this could be tight! Afridi hits it straight to Taylor at cover and takes off immediately. There was no single in there. Once Taylor hit, it was over for him. He gets a standing ovation for a superb 61

commentPreTextItems.html: Umar Gul has his helmet on but i don't think it's needed now

commentTextItems.html: short ball, Sohail finishes it with a boundary over fine-leg. Fantastic knock from Sohail and he deservingly gets to hit the winning runs

commentPostTextItems.html: That's all from our coverage here. We will be back for the next ODI. Thanks for all the comments and feedback. Ciao ciao.

"Very tough game. After we lost Hafeez as a bowler, it was difficult to get the fifth bowler," Misbah-ul-Haq says. "The way Haris and Shahid went about it, it was really a wonderful performance. We are looking to try different things because this is the last series before WC. We will try more things in coming games. We have to take chances at this stage. Sarfraz could be really helpful down the order, he plays spin and big shots under pressure really well.. we are looking for that role for him in Australia. The partnership was really special. The temperament of Haris for the way he bowled for very good. And that helped him well in batting as well. And Shahid played a tremendous knock according to the situation."

"Yeah, I think on the back of Ross' superb knock we had a reasonable total on the board but we didn't do the job well with the ball," says Kane Williamson. "We picked up the wickets early but couldn't finish the job. There are some positives, lot of things to learn by playing in this part of the world. Pakistan played extremely well and deserved to win. Vettori's was an outstanding catch and an important one too. We certainly want to win every game we play, we want to put out this team as much as possible."

"I tried my best. Thanks to Shahid bhai, it didn't feel like I was playing in international cricket during that stand," Haris Sohail, who is the Man of the Match, says. "He supported me really well. Vicky bhai and Mushy bhai gave me confidence.. they told me that I would bowl. I wanted to play a long innings like this and it worked out well."

A wonderful contest. New Zealand had the upper hand once they dismissed the first six Pakistan batsmen for only 124. But then that partnership  between Haris Sohail and Shahid Afridi - uncharacteristic in its flair but utter important.. It slowly ground New Zealand out. That after New Zealand's innings had followed the same pattern with Ross Taylor leading them to 246. Sohail, in fact, played the mirror role perfectly to bring up his maiden half-century... and what an important one that was! Add to that his 10 overs of economical bowling. Pakistan would also have been pleasantly surprised by the restraint Afridi showed during the chase, scoring 61 important runs.

lefty: "poor captaincy by Williamson. Fine leg and third man needed to be much finer for at least the last 5 overs. Needed a short cover and short mid wicket for the same period. And once it got down to a run a ball had to have the most of the fielders stopping one. Elementary stuff really"
Saad: "Happy to see team didn't rely on the bigs Younis and Misbah to bail them out. They took responsibility."

commentTextItems.html: slower delivery on the pads, Riaz dabs it to square leg for a quick single to level the scores

commentPreTextItems.html: Easy from here. Three runs are all they need. Neesham in conference with Williamson.

commentTextItems.html: short delivery outside off, the batsman ramps it to third man for an easy single
looks to swing down the ground but misses it completely.. Mills keeps appealing for a caught behind but no one else shows interest

headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: nicely crashes it to third man and calls for a second as it's Vettori down there. The throw comes in at the striker's end.. Could be a run-out..It's a tough one.. His dive has saved him
quicker delivery outside off, past the outside edge
poor ball from Mills, this is on the pads and all Wahab has to do is to get some bat on it.. That he does, with the fine leg up, there is no one there to stop it
he gets off strike with a push to long-on.. Sohail trusts Riaz and asks him to come back for the second as the fielder is a bit deep
back of length on the pads, clipped to short fine leg for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: Wahab Riaz comes in. 13 off 13 needed

commentTextItems.html: short delivery outside off, Sohail ramps it to third-man for a single

commentPostTextItems.html: Xaideez: "@Kashid Siddiqui : Indeed it was restored:)"

commentPreTextItems.html: Kashif Siddiqui: "Boom Boom services have been restored! We apologize for any inconvenience that it may have caused. Thank you for your patience!"

commentTextItems.html: direct hit and this could be tight! Afridi hits it straight to Taylor at cover and takes off immediately. There was no single in there. Once Taylor hit, it was over for him. He gets a standing ovation for a superb 61

commentPostTextItems.html: Afridi, though, is a bit disappointed for not closing out this game
Awais Sohrab: "STAT : 2nd time in Afridi's 50 plus runs innings that he completed 50 runs without hitting a 6. Last time, 53 vs WI in 1997. "

commentTextItems.html: short outside off and this has been roundhouse kicked through square leg. Slapped over the fielder at square leg
comes down the pitch and dabs the short delivery to cover for a quick single. A throw comes in at Afrid's end but Williamson misses. Afridi is not happy with that call
short delivery outside off, Sohail gets out of the way too early.. Realises later he could have just steered it to third man
another slower delivery, this is sliced to deep backward point for a couple

commentPreTextItems.html: I have got a feeling that there are not calm shots left in Afridi's bag anymore

commentTextItems.html: slower delivery wide outside off, goes over the wide marker.. the umpire calls in favour of the batsman

commentPreTextItems.html: Allen: "For me Sohail should be the MOM. The maturity shown in this innings with his wonderfully economical 10 overs consisting of 30 dots and conceding only a single boundary. He has shown the rest of the team how to play.. Everything said, I want New Zealand to win... :-P :-D"

commentTextItems.html: the Afridi is in town! The length doesn't matter.. Afridi just goes with the big shot and although it looks like he hasn't got enough, it actually just eludes the long-on fielder..

headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Mark: "Neesham is a mixed bag. He bowls too many wides and no-balls to be a good death bowler but he does have a knack of sometimes picking up lucky wickets. Hope he can do so here."

commentTextItems.html: slower delivery outside off, Afridi wanted to smash it through point but is beaten
fuller on off, he brings his fifty not with a six but with a calm push to deep midwicket for two. He applauds his partner.. The dressing room is up to applaud the innings too
moves to the leg side again and drags the short ball to midwicket for a single

dismissalComment.html: oh he's given it away and that's a great catch from Younis running back! It was a short ball again, Ronchi pulled half-heartedly and the leading edge went high on the leg side. Younis ran towards the boundary from midwicket and caught it with a dive near the 30-yard circle with this arms stretched outwards

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori b Wahab Riaz 27 (25b 3x4 0x6 35m) SR: 108

dismissalComment.html: bang on target, hits the stumps! Wahab replies with a superb ball on the stumps and Vettori misses it this time. He shuffled too far across for the full delivery that was swinging in towards middle, looked to work it on leg but missed and was bowled the way he was in the 2nd T20

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez b Mills 6 (17b 0x4 0x6 22m) SR: 35.29

dismissalComment.html: superb delivery to get rid of Hafeez, who was not looking good today! It had the scrambled seam on length outside off, Hafeez moved towards the ball and left a gap between bat and ball which the ball sneaked through, deflected off the pad and hit the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad lbw b Vettori 28 (41b 5x4 0x6 54m) SR: 68.29

dismissalComment.html: Vettori has struck, Shehzad is gone! That was the arm ball sliding in towards the stumps from outside off, Shehzad went way back in the crease and covered his stumps, the ball came in struck him right in front of the stumps past the bat, finger went up immediately. Pakistan decide not to review it

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq c Devcich b Neesham 5 (17b 0x4 0x6 27m) SR: 29.41

dismissalComment.html: that's a simple catch for Devcich at point, Shafiq's scratchy innings is over! Short of good length outside off, he cut it straight to Devcich for a waist-high catch

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c Brownlie b Vettori 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 25m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: oh another one! Younis has swept this straight to deep backward square leg. It was a late decision on Younis' part. He was upright and went down very quickly, possibly that was the reason he didn't get the control on it. Hits it hard, hits it flat .. straight to the fielder

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail not out 85 (109b 5x4 1x6 158m) SR: 77.98

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c Vettori b Neesham 13 (23b 1x4 0x6 24m) SR: 56.52

dismissalComment.html: oh my Vettori! What a stunner that is! And we thought he had fitness issues! Misbah wanted to go over the infield but gets a toe-end to his attempted loft.. But this was still going away from Vettori at mid-on.. He runs backwards and stretches his left-arm out to pluck out this one from nowhere. Excellent grab

dismissalText.commentary: Sarfaraz Ahmed c Milne b McCullum 26 (19b 3x4 0x6 20m) SR: 136.84

dismissalComment.html: is that the end of the challenge! Sir Faraz wanted to whack it over wide long-on.. Just didn't get enough of it. The fielder was standing right at the edge of the boundary and Milne gobbles it up.

headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi run out (Taylor) 61 (51b 7x4 1x6 81m) SR: 119.6

dismissalComment.html: direct hit and this could be tight! Afridi hits it straight to Taylor at cover and takes off immediately. There was no single in there. Once Taylor hit, it was over for him. He gets a standing ovation for a superb 61
